[[BODY
<h3>Takeaways from the <a href="http://berner-architekten-treffen.ch">BAT</a> meetup #30 - Agile Architecture</h3>

<p>Beeing agile:
<ul>
  <li>adaptable to changing requirements</li>
  <li>orientation towards uncertainty</li>
  <li>learn and teach by <a href="http://martinfowler.com/bliki/ShuHaRi.html">ShuHaRi</a></li>
</ul>
</p>


<p>Architectural aspects:
<ul>
  <li>cross-cutting requirements and decisions</li>
  <li>conceptual integrity</li>
  <li>risk minimization</li>
</ul>
</p>


<p>The architect:
<ul>
  <li>actively facilitates communication</li>
  <li>acts as a service provider and supporter</li>
  <li>postpones decisions until the last reasonable moment (keeping options open)</li>
  <li>solves todays problems and doesn't create to many new ones for the future (balancing of technical debts)</li>
  <li>promotes routine</li>
  <li>enforces guidelines</li>
</ul>
</p>

BODY]]
